Overfitting and Underfitting

Studied the concepts of Overfitting and Underfitting in Decision Trees.

Learned that:

Overfitting occurs when the tree becomes too complex and memorizes the training data.
Underfitting occurs when the tree is too simple and fails to capture important patterns.

Discussed techniques to prevent overfitting, including:

Limiting tree depth
Setting minimum samples per leaf
Setting minimum samples required for splitting
Tree pruning
Tree Pruning

Received an introduction to Pruning, the process of reducing unnecessary branches in a Decision Tree.

Learned that pruning:

Reduces overfitting.
Improves model generalization.
Makes the tree simpler and easier to interpret.

Discussed pre-pruning and post-pruning techniques.

